<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870601-0169 </DOCNO><HL> Western Union Plans PactTo Extend Debt Maturities</HL><DD> 06/01/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><CO> WU WUT+ </CO><IN> BOND MARKET NEWS (BON) </IN><DATELINE> UPPER SADDLE RIVER, N.J.  </DATELINE><TEXT>    Western Union Corp. said itexpects to sign agreements this week extending until Nov. 13maturities on certain bank loans and on senior notes of itstelegraph company subsidiary.   Both sets of obligations were to expire Friday, but banks granted a one-week extension to complete paperwork, the communications company said.    Western Union announced a restructuring plan last month under which New York investor Bennett S. LeBow would take control of the company after buying ITT Corp.'s international telex business and merging it with Western Union. </TEXT></DOC>